Why I used langchain-core and lngchain-groq next to langgraph?

I used LangGraph as the orchestration layer because the assessment 
required a multi-step workflow. I used LangChain’s Groq integration 
only as the LLM client layer, because it gave me a clean way to 
call Groq and enforce structured output through Pydantic. 
This kept the workflow modular: LangGraph manages process flow, 
Groq handles language understanding, and Python rules handle 
routing and escalation.

LangGraph = workflow orchestration
LangChain Core = message structure
LangChain Groq = Groq LLM connection
Pydantic = validation of the LLM result





What is FastAPI?

FastAPI is a Python web framework used to build APIs.
Where our backend layer does the workflow through HTTP endpoints like:
POST /triage
POST /triage/samples
GET /results
DELETE /results


Why FastAPI? and not Flask?

We used FastAPI because this project is supposed to simulate a 
real AI automation workflow. In a company, the workflow would 
usually be triggered by another system: support portal, CRM, 
webhook, form submission, or internal tool.

I used FastAPI instead of Flask because the workflow is 
schema-driven. FastAPI integrates directly with Pydantic, 
automatically validates request and response models, and 
provides interactive API documentation through /docs.